<br>
I'm done here.  I've completly spelled out why it would be bad for some of the things warriors want and agreed with some of the points they make.  I'm sorry if you don't feel defensive and evasive are good enough disc's to balance you out.  Your taking them for granted and that is something I can't help.  <br>
<br>
I'm not worried about warriors getting most of the stuff they are asking for, because I believe the designers at verant understand the balance of classes now and are no longer going to skew things in favor of one class as previously.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry if you thought that before SoL paladins &quot;whined&quot; alot on our boards.  If you have spent as much time lfg watching warriors get spots, or being near useless at raids you would have spoken up too.  Paladins feel that we are now balanced with warriors.  When you add up the sum of the two classes they both have jobs to do and both are useful/needed.  <br>
<br>
Before luclin came out I was a big supporter of paladins getting defensive.  I see how that would be wrong now though.  The only thing I'd ask for at all would be to have ToK and DS fixed.  Both are broken but verant has decided to ignore them.  No biggie though cause overall we are a happy class.  <br>
<br>
As the singer said &quot;it's not getting what you want, but wanting what you've got&quot;<br>
