60 Crusader<br>
Druzzil Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufrodlin7th.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frodlin7th</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 6:05:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=402>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   God</span><hr size=1> This is really interesting.  I have seen NO arguments against putting monks on a higher offensive table than all other melee, why such a fuss about doing the SAME thing for the ONLY pure defensive MELEE ONLY class in the game with the defensive table?<br>
<br>
I'll tell you why.  Because Paladins and SK's are scared.  Irrationaly so I might add.  Almost hysterically so.  You're scared that rebalancing warriors would put you in the same position that you were in Kunark.  This is UTTERLY FALSE.  <br>
<br>
You guys had it REAL bad in Kunark, no one has denied this once.  But, your balancing didn't occur with the &quot;melee balancing&quot; patch.... it occurred in waves, and it was overdone when the sum of all parts was added together.<br>
<br>
- Exp Penalty done away with<br>
<br>
- Mana pool drastically increased <br>
<br>
- Defensive table adjusted <br>
<br>
- Spell casting during combat adjusted<br>
<br>
- Pal/SK only weapons introduced with drastically superior stats<br>
<br>
- 2 Hand damage upgrade<br>
<br>
- Hybrid OFFENSE upgrades<br>
<br>
- New Spells at every expansion<br>
<br>
- All/All or Melee/All Equipment which completely obliterated equipment based superiority<br>
<br>
- AC Soft Cap Stopping the progression of warriors<br>
<br>
- AAXP....this one is HUGE.  Did you know that warriors did not get a SINGLE defense based AA class skill?  NOT ONE, and Defense is our lifeblood.  Paladins/SK's not only got the SAME defensive AA skills as warriors, but to compound it, they got an addition class skill which FURTHER erodes into the difference.<br>
<br>
-Priest AA Archetype skills.  Again, on the surface, this doesn't seem like much, but it's in essence, quadruple regen for Paladins.<br>
<br>
Ok, so to improve warriors' defense to such a degree that there's some real difference, would NOT throw Paladins &quot;back to where they were before&quot;.  The only way that this would happen is if there were an introduction of mobs which based on the difference, that a Paladin COULD NOT function, as was the case before.   The problem with Paladins before was that they sucked....BAD.  They were broken in SO many areas that it wasn't even funny.  This is not only no longer the case, but it's come to the point where they are WAY more powerful overall than warriors, and have encroached even onto warriors' sacred ground.... Melee defense.  When there's not enough difference to make a clear choice on a melee based skill between a pure melee and a hybrid... THE MELEE IS BROKEN.<br>
<br>
You should NOT be chosen based on your defensive tanking skills, but based on your inherent group value.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
