Crusader of Brell<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udobbanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dobbanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/7/02 10:13:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=404>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: God</span><hr size=1> Someone earlier asked how monks could possibly tank better than a warrior in an exp setting. Ill tell you why. Just from my gear which is BARELY average if not a bit below, I have 1602hp/936 ac. Not too impressed? Well counting mend which heals 25% of my life every few minutes I now have a total of 2000 hp to tank with. On top of that monks on average get hit 8% less than a warrior. The fact that we can solo so effectively should show you what decent tanks we are unbuffed. Now as I said, my gear is barely average at 52 for a monk. There are a number of monks on the top end guilds that are topping 4khp unbuffed and hitting the 1400 ac mark with ease. When you take into consideration the 8% less damage taken you have a tank capable of staying alive through almost any fight. About the only thing keeping a monk from being mt in a raid is that lack of a reliable taunt. Sure we deal out massive taunt just by virtue of the insane amounts of damage we deal but since we have no reliable way to pull an uber mob off a caster fast we just shouldnt be in that situation.<br>
In an exp group though, I can be mt just fine. When it comes to killing dark blues monks are probably the best tanks around. We get to deal out our full amount of damage, we take much less damage than your average tank, and by having a monk there the mob will die much faster than if it was a warrior standing there.<br>
Back to the subject of this incredibly long debate, I had said way back on one of the earlier pages that my personal thought would be to put warriors on a new defensive table. One that wouldnt be HUGELY better but still noticeable. Just enough so that if it came down to whether that 56 paladin, 56 monk, or 56 warrior should be mt, you would pick the warrior just for the slight advantage. I have news for you pallys, you arent broken anymore, there is no need to worry that actually improving the warrior class will make you somehow worthless. Warriors ARE supposed to be preffered as main tanks over all others. You may not like the fact but its true. You wont go back to the days when people would giggle if you offered yourself as a tank because you are now very effective at tanking. I dont even PLAY a warrior and I think warriors should be the first choice when it comes to tanking. <br>
I think improving the taunt would make the game a bit too easy personally though, mainly because if taunt worked any better than it already does, at least at 60, then it would be far too easy for a warrior to hold agro even over chain nukers and healers. I dont know about agro from 51 to 59 since my guilds mt is a warlord but at least in exp groups, unless I am a couple levels above the warrior or he is using really crappy weapons, he can normally hold agro off me when he is supposed to. Once again, it sounds like for raids its different, I wouldnt know because I normally only have 60 warriors as mt in my raids.<br>
Ah well, ive rambled on long enough. This has deviated far from its origional purpose,(thank you paladins) so hopefully this will put it back online.<br>
