 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchavr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>chavr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/02 12:21:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=406>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: God</span><hr size=1> Ok, so I was wrong, I am posting again.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have seen NO arguments against putting monks on a higher offensive table than all other melee, why such a fuss about doing the SAME thing for the ONLY pure defensive MELEE ONLY class in the game with the defensive table?&quot;<br>
<br>
Offense stacks, defense doesn't.  How many tanks do you need in one exp group?  How many damage dealers do you want?  Nuff said.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Exp Penalty done away with- yes, but warriors still have an exp bonus.<br>
<br>
- Mana pool drastically increased- All that was done was penalties removed.  We received no special upgrades.<br>
<br>
- Defensive table adjusted- Yes, but our other mitigation skills are still capped lower then a warrior.<br>
<br>
- Spell casting during combat adjusted- Yeah, because casting during a fight would half your dps.  If you didn't time spells just right you seriously cramped damage output.  We still can't fight while casting, but we no longer reset wpn dly on every cast.<br>
<br>
- Pal/SK only weapons introduced with drastically superior stats- Our wpns were subpar previously and warriors have gotten new wpns with superior stats on them compared to previous expansions.  Even with these new wpns you talk of we do less dps then a warrior.<br>
<br>
- 2 Hand damage upgrade-  This affects every single class that uses a 2hdr and not just knights. In other words warriors got this upgrade also.  If 2hdrs really are that much better now perhaps you should try using one.<br>
<br>
- Hybrid OFFENSE upgrades- paladins still capped at 225.  yep, still lower then a warrior by a good bit.  Turn on others misses one day and stand next to a paladin fighting.  You'll get a good laugh out of it.<br>
<br>
- New Spells at every expansion- Yes, and warriors have gotten new armor and wpns at every expansion.  We are part fighter and part caster.  They both have to be maintained as the game grows.<br>
<br>
- All/All or Melee/All Equipment which completely obliterated equipment based superiorit-  Agreed.  No problems at all with making more warrior gear to fit their needs.  Gear isn't a huge balancing area.  <br>
<br>
- AC Soft Cap Stopping the progression of warriors-  Show me raw, hard data from verant on the soft caps per class and how they affect gameplay.  Sorry, but this isn't something you can point to and say it's imbalanced.  There is just too much speculation and not enough hard facts for it.  This deserves looking into, but isn't really a valid argument for this topic.<br>
<br>
AA skills-  I checked out the list of warrior skills.  They looked like some nice stuff to help increase your damage.  I could understand warriors being miffed some about PE though and I dont' think it would warp the balance if warriors were to get it.  2% isn't that much of a boost to really have much of an affect in the long run.  You may think paladins have better skills, we may think you have better skills, but in the end the skills are pretty much balanced out.  We get a mixture of utiltiy type skills to be selected on how we want to shape our character, and you get mainly damage upgrade skills.  <br>
<br>
Saying we get priest skills too and implying that is bad is ridiculous.  We are both a fighter and a caster.  We are not the best at either, but we are able to do some of both.  Once again, you can't neglect one of the parts because you will ruin the whole if you do.<br>
<br>
Remember also.  When chosing gear hybrids have to worry about more then just hp/ac/sta.  We have to add in wis/int/mana too.  Factor in focus effects for either our melee side or our casting side.  It's difficult to find a balance in gear for us with all the things we have to watch out for.  <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;You should NOT be chosen based on your defensive tanking skills, but based on your inherent group value.&quot;<br>
<br>
What exactly is our inherent group value?  What is the spot you would have us fill?  Lets break down your average exp group.<br>
<br>
Cleric/druid -more then likely a cleric, but you have to have a healer<br>
<br>
Chanter/bard/shaman -mana regen/crowd control/haste/slows... someone has to do it<br>
<br>
Warrior/paladin/shadowknight -Tank, someone has to take the hits in there.<br>
<br>
Monk/rogue/ranger/mage/wizard/necro/beastlord/warrior- these are your damage dealing classes.  They fill up the last 3 spots.  <br>
<br>
Now then, if you were to make warriors the best tanks you can drop the knights out.  You can't stick them in with the dps classes, because we have the lowest dps out of all those.  Warriors do about 40% more dps in comparable gear if memory serves correctly.  <br>
<br>
So where exactly would you have the knight classes go?  Where is our inherent group value?  Shadowknights could take a monk spot for pulling sometimes.  They also have offense based spells that are good when a necro isn't around.  So they will be able to get some groups.  <br>
<br>
Paladins though don't have a special ability like feign death.  Our strength lies in our healing when it comes to spells.  Healing doesn't really stack though because you can only heal so much before everyone is full health.  You don't need 2 clerics in groups because one is able to keep up with heals.  You don't need a cleric and a paladin to keep up with heals because a cleric is plenty.  How many times in an exp group have you asked for a backup healer?  How many times have you looked for added dps?  It makes more sense to invite someone that will help you kill mobs faster rather then someone that can backup heal.  Remember that paladins do about half or less damage when compared to rogues/rangers/monks.  That is a huge difference in damage output and a much longer fight.  <br>
<br>
So what exactly would you have us offer a group if we aren't desired as a tank?  Tell me how I will still be desired once it is known that warriors are once again the best tanks and a group is much better off with a war for tanking rather than a paladin.<br>
<br>
<br>
