<br>
Those disciplines were given to us in an era when AC meant something. Even at the end of Kunark the most uber warriors (i.e. Me and a small handful of others) could barely reach the AC softcap, a cap which was never raised in Velious and only marginally increased in SoL - over two years later. Conversely, the average fight times versus uber mobs were raised almost exponentially while the DPM from mobs barely changed; and in MANY Velious and even Luclin uber encounters, remained BELOW the DPM of Dragons in Veeshan's Peak - the Vision took a wicked, wicked wrong turn in game design. How could they have not seen this mess coming?<br>
<br>
In those days, the term monk and tank were only used in the same sentence when you were talking about what it felt like to get rolled over by a twenty ton tank if you were a monk that tried to tackle anything larger than a bread box, head on.<br>
<br>
Additionally, due to the fact that fights hardly ever lasted more than 4-5 minutes, the disciplines made sense - two years ago.<br>
<br>
Right now they are only a vestige; a remnant of a bygone era: A time when Armor Class meant something and the warrior class was more than a mish mash of bad coding and lost grey matter.<br>
